## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Solution using ***HashMap.***
- First, we took a map *mp* and initialize all characters with -1.`for(auto x:s) mp[x] = -1;`
- Then we took start to keep track the last position of a character, initialize with -1.
- if a character in map has a value greater than start that means it is already present in some previous index, so update start with the previous index value.
`if(mp[s[i]] > start) start = mp[s[i]];`
- We’ll update the character value in the map with the present index & calculate the maximum length by taking the maximum of ans and i-start, which indicates the last index to the current index where no character is repeating. `ans = max(ans, i-start)`
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLongestSubstring(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        unordered_map<char, int> mp;
        for(auto x:s)
            mp[x] = -1;

        int i=0, start=-1, ans=0;
        while(i<n){
            if(mp[s[i]] > start)
                start = mp[s[i]];
            mp[s[i]] = i;
            ans = max(ans, i-start);
            i++;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

